news.headline: Lodash Logo Lodash 中文文档
news.content:
Lodash 是一个一致性、模块化、高性能的 JavaScript 实用工具库。

Lodash 遵循 MIT 开源协议发布，并且支持最新的运行环境。 查看各个构件版本的区别并选择一个适合你的版本。

安装​

浏览器环境：


<script src="lodash.js"></script>

通过 npm：


$ npm i -g npm$ npm i --save lodash

Node.js：


// Load the full build.var _ = require('lodash');// Load the core build.var _ = require('lodash/core');// Load the FP build for immutable auto-curried iteratee-first data-last methods.var fp = require('lodash/fp'); // Load method categories.var array = require('lodash/array');var object = require('lodash/fp/object'); // Cherry-pick methods for smaller browserify/rollup/webpack bundles.var at = require('lodash/at');var curryN = require('lodash/fp/curryN');



注意：

如需在 Node.js < 6 的 REPL 环境中使用 Lodash，请安装 n_。

为什么选择 Lodash ？​

Lodash 通过降低 array、number、objects、string 等等的使用难度从而让 JavaScript 变得更简单。 Lodash 的模块化方法 非常适用于：

  • 遍历 array、object 和 string
  • 对值进行操作和检测
  • 创建符合功能的函数

模块格式​

Lodash 提供 多种构建方式 和模块格式。

  • lodash & per method packages
  • lodash-es, babel-plugin-lodash, & lodash-webpack-plugin
  • lodash/fp
  • lodash-amd

补充工具​

  • futil-js 是一套用来补足 lodash 的实用工具集。

扩展阅读​

  • 贡献
  • 版本说明
  • Wiki（更新记录、路线图等）

兼容性​

在 Chrome 74-75、Firefox 66-67、IE 11、Edge 18、Safari 11-12 和 Node.js 8-12 环境中测试

news.headline: HTML5+CSS3视频教程
news.content:
Hello，各位锋迷们，有个好消息要告诉大家~

千锋前端金牌讲师Kerwin又出新品：《HTML5+CSS3视频教程》，扫码一键直达课程

本套前端教程，专门为零基础小白人员精心制作，为大家详细解答新手学习所遇到的各种web前端技术问题，循序渐进学Web前端，为进阶提升打下夯实的基础。

主讲大咖Kerwin

Kerwin老师曾就职于IBM，获得IBM WORKLIGHT跨平台移动应用高级开发者认证，致力于移动应用开发以及多种基础平台整合的企业级解决方案。

熟悉Kerwin老师的同学都知道，他不仅人长得帅，讲的课更是有意思，课程一大特色就是评书式教学，听课就好比听相声，风趣幽默，简直不要太郭德纲！

课程介绍

5G时代，人工智能，大数据，云计算带领人类进入新的维度，我们在平行时空里思考，在终端中交互实现，而HTML5作为万维网的核心标准，赋予了终端前所未有的兼容性和能力，踏入web开发的世界，就是走进了未来，HTML5就是价值源头。

HTML5+CSS3视频教程将会基于2021年最新Web标准录制，包含所有HTML5+CSS3的新特性，传统布局和弹性盒布局、响应式布局、网格布局深入讲解，打造一站式知识长龙服务。

products.title: A 3D printer that prints cookies
products.introduction: Food PrinterOrdinary food can be printed in a variety of shapes, and users can choose food shapes directly from the machine's touch display, download from the Internet or import designs they have saved in USB.
products.detail: Essentially, it's a 3D printer, but unlike regular 3D printers that print plastic into models, this printer is able to turn ingredients into semi-finished food. Whether the toppings are chocolate, dough or other solid items, what is currently printed is a cookie or cake topping. But you have to bake the prints before you can eat them.

products.title: A brain wave tracker
products.introduction: myBrain Technologies' Melomind headset, which was a hit at CES, uses sensors to measure your brain waves and sends the data in real time to a mobile app that plays music tailored to the user's mood
products.detail: The music was all composed by sound designers at myBrain Technologies. When the user gradually enters a relaxed state, he can control the type of music he hears.

products.title: Electric shock proof socket
products.introduction: The Brio is an anti-shock and energy-saving power outlet that costs $50 for a regular version.
products.detail: Built-in sensors can sense if a device is plugged in or if a child's finger accidentally touches the socket; It can also remotely monitor your home for fires or leaks.

products.title: Good news for foodies: self-tightening belts
products.introduction: This is a smart belt that automatically adjusts the tightness based on your food intake and exercise for the day.
products.detail: It also reminds you to get up and move when you've been sitting for too long. Betly, from French startup Emiota, uses small sensors, accelerators and gyroscopes to monitor exactly how long you're moving and when you need to sit up to warm up. Betly automatically expands and expands according to your waistline, so there's no need to worry about how your waistline will change over the next few years.
